CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 12, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Left by Coleses - This is the home left by Maggie and James Coles at 17 Watt St. It has been well kept up inside and out, by the survivors."
TitMainTitle: Two story brick house with antenna on chimney, and yard with chain link fence, 17 Watt Street, Hill District
